02:53.120 --> 03:02.640
written like this. In general, a classical system of n bits can only ever be in just one of 2 to the n possible

26
03:02.640 --> 03:10.959
combinations of zeros and ones. A quantum system of n cubits can be in a superposition of all 2 to the n of these

27
03:10.959 --> 03:17.519
states. The scaling is exponential. So even if we had just 10 cubits, they

28
03:17.519 --> 03:25.599
could be in a superposition state of 2 to the 10, which is 1,024 possible combinations of zeros and

