parallelism and is partially responsible for the advantage of quantum computers over classical computers. But a quantum

31
03:39.440 --> 03:46.480
computer is not just a massive parallel processor. Just because the cubits in a quantum computer can be in a

32
03:46.480 --> 03:53.519
superposition of exponentially many states doesn't mean we have access to all the information in each of these

33
03:53.519 --> 03:59.760
states. Since measurement collapses the system into one state or another, let's

34
03:59.760 --> 04:06.799
see how this plays out in a simple problem. Say there's some machine that

