10:22.640 --> 10:28.640
care about its state at all, then the second hatomard here just undoes what

89
10:28.640 --> 10:37.279
the first hatamard did. And we'll measure the cubit to be in the state zero. Let's look at the balanced function f_sub_2 as an example to see

90
10:37.279 --> 10:44.079
what uf does to the state in this case. When x is zero, f ofx is zero and when x

91
10:44.079 --> 10:50.399
is 1, f ofx is 1. Remember what I told you about the ufgate. It takes cubit 0

92
10:50.399 --> 10:56.800
as our input x state and outputs f ofx on cubit 1. Assuming that cubit 1

